585
01:20:06,687 --> 01:20:10,566
That is good, it cures.

586
01:20:10,567 --> 01:20:16,567
You are my brother.

587
01:20:37,687 --> 01:20:40,846
Are you sending money
for my sister's health treatment?

588
01:20:40,847 --> 01:20:44,446
Every first in the month.

589
01:20:44,447 --> 01:20:47,646
For the house too.
The foundation has already been laid.

590
01:20:47,647 --> 01:20:51,486
Now they're building walls.

591
01:20:51,487 --> 01:20:57,487
I only have you and Robert left.

592
01:21:13,807 --> 01:21:19,807
Dzamila.

593
01:21:29,927 --> 01:21:35,927
Everyone come here!

594
01:21:37,327 --> 01:21:40,286
From today on Perhan is
the parade commander.

595
01:21:40,287 --> 01:21:46,287
Obey him more then Zef
or Sadama. Is that clear?

596
01:24:05,327 --> 01:24:09,966
Young man!

597
01:24:09,967 --> 01:24:14,326
Are you looking for someone?

598
01:24:14,327 --> 01:24:17,326
They are now mine.
Do you know that?

599
01:24:17,327 --> 01:24:23,327
Look.

600
01:24:27,807 --> 01:24:34,280
Tell the big boss,
that Sadam is not crazy,

601
01:24:34,487 --> 01:24:40,487
to rot in jail because
of him.

602
01:24:40,767 --> 01:24:44,606
You know, I put the guilt
on Zef. And he,

603
01:24:44,607 --> 01:24:47,726
as it befits for the younger
brother,

604
01:24:47,727 --> 01:24:53,727
took all the blame on himself.

605
01:24:54,527 --> 01:25:00,527
Ciao, handsoome.

606
01:25:11,927 --> 01:25:17,646
Fuck that luck.

607
01:25:17,647 --> 01:25:22,126
Buy ones like these.
For the business.

608
01:25:22,127 --> 01:25:24,686
Some baby.

609
01:25:24,687 --> 01:25:29,686
And some pregnant woman.
It's easier to get across the border.

610
01:25:29,687 --> 01:25:32,526
My God, look.
An entirely different person.

611
01:25:32,527 --> 01:25:36,846
Something of each if it's possible.
That's the best.

612
01:25:36,847 --> 01:25:39,206
May God bless you,
I'm counting on you.

613
01:25:39,207 --> 01:25:42,286
Where is that house of mine,
that is being built?

614
01:25:42,287 --> 01:25:44,526
I would like to see the construction.

615
01:25:44,527 --> 01:25:47,486
House? Next to mine.

616
01:25:47,487 --> 01:25:50,526
Where else would it be?
Are we brothers or not?

617
01:25:50,527 --> 01:25:54,326
But you musn't go to our place.
- Why not?

618
01:25:54,327 --> 01:26:00,327
That's what the lawyer said,
that acuired the passport for you.

619
01:26:02,087 --> 01:26:04,246
There's a big confusion.

620
01:26:04,247 --> 01:26:07,046
It's being reported in newspapers,
on radio, TV.

621
01:26:07,047 --> 01:26:11,086
They've made a movie about people,
that sell children abroad.

622
01:26:11,087 --> 01:26:13,686
Don't go there, please.

623
01:26:13,687 --> 01:26:17,486
Go to the ferryboat Bari-Bar,
and then to Monte Negro and Bosnia.

624
01:26:17,487 --> 01:26:20,526
I wanted to see grandma
and Azra,

625
01:26:20,527 --> 01:26:22,446
to visit my sister in Ljubljana.

626
01:26:22,447 --> 01:26:25,006
No, by no means, please.

627
01:26:25,007 --> 01:26:31,007
Only to the south. He're the address of
a man from Tuzla.

628
01:26:35,327 --> 01:26:38,286
Find a wife for me.

629
01:26:38,287 --> 01:26:42,326
I'll sen Dzamila away.
Rate her as you would rate her for yourself.

630
01:26:42,327 --> 01:26:48,327
Go, good luck.

631
01:28:22,847 --> 01:28:25,086
Come here!

632
01:28:25,087 --> 01:28:27,326
I'm not guilty,
I don't know anything.

633
01:28:27,327 --> 01:28:31,166
May I get blind if i know anything.
I don't know anything.

634
01:28:31,167 --> 01:28:34,246
I've come as it befits.

635
01:28:34,247 --> 01:28:37,606
Oh my. Billions!

636
01:28:37,607 --> 01:28:42,046
I don't have to kiss hands.
- Is this for me?

637
01:28:42,047 --> 01:28:44,926
Look at him the big businessman.

638
01:28:44,927 --> 01:28:48,846
How did you earn that much money?

639
01:28:48,847 --> 01:28:54,847
He came so he would trick my daughter
with the money.

640
01:28:54,847 --> 01:28:57,766
Look!

641
01:28:57,767 --> 01:29:03,767
Did she get married? -No.

642
01:29:08,047 --> 01:29:10,726
What can I do.
Woman like woman.

643
01:29:10,727 --> 01:29:13,286
She did what she decided.

644
01:29:13,287 --> 01:29:16,766
I don't know how to deal with her.

645
01:29:16,767 --> 01:29:20,446
I wonder myself.
What should I do with her?

646
01:29:20,447 --> 01:29:24,086
I don't know myself!

647
01:29:24,087 --> 01:29:26,286
And the child she bears?

648
01:29:26,287 --> 01:29:32,287
It's supposably yours.

649
01:29:35,287 --> 01:29:41,287
What do you think?
- Ask your uncle.

650
01:29:44,487 --> 01:29:50,487
God, what are you doing to me?

651
01:29:56,127 --> 01:30:00,406
A black train has come mother.

652
01:30:00,407 --> 01:30:04,326
It has come, mother,

653
01:30:04,327 --> 01:30:10,327
a black morning.

654
01:30:40,407 --> 01:30:42,726
Neighbour, there is no sense
in drinking that much.

655
01:30:42,727 --> 01:30:46,286
I also drank brandy,
but it doesn't help.

656
01:30:46,287 --> 01:30:52,287
Look, the drink has changed you
into a woman.

657
01:32:05,207 --> 01:32:08,886
Like you aren't happy,
to see me.

658
01:32:08,887 --> 01:32:11,366
Grandma loves you.

659
01:32:11,367 --> 01:32:17,367
What are you doing to your head?

660
01:32:24,287 --> 01:32:30,287
Come, don't be afraid.
You've come with me.

661
01:32:35,127 --> 01:32:37,646
What lays on your heart, grandma?

662
01:32:37,647 --> 01:32:41,046
Mine is fine.
What's with yours?

663
01:32:41,047 --> 01:32:43,806
Where did you leave your sister?

664
01:32:43,807 --> 01:32:47,966
In Ljubljana. She should
return back soon.

665
01:32:47,967 --> 01:32:52,086
Bring me a glass of brandy.

666
01:32:52,087 --> 01:32:58,087
You take the chair and sit down.

667
01:33:04,327 --> 01:33:07,326
Why does your wife cry?

668
01:33:07,327 --> 01:33:11,246
The bitch has to let out water,
and she releases it through her eyes.

669
01:33:11,247 --> 01:33:14,446
Why do you trust your mother-in-law
more then your wife?

670
01:33:14,447 --> 01:33:16,926
Since I've got myself lying,

671
01:33:16,927 --> 01:33:19,926
I don't trust noone anymore.

672
01:33:19,927 --> 01:33:23,406
If you don't trust at all,
God will abandon you.

673
01:33:23,407 --> 01:33:29,407
Where did you get this?
Where did you get these clothes?

674
01:33:31,527 --> 01:33:34,886
I've earned it with these
ten fingers.

675
01:33:34,887 --> 01:33:37,206
I will build a house
with them as well.

676
01:33:37,207 --> 01:33:40,886
Who will live in this house?

677
01:33:40,887 --> 01:33:46,887
You and me, grandma.

678
01:33:46,967 --> 01:33:51,206
I will not live in this house.
My spirit doesn't want to.

679
01:33:51,207 --> 01:33:54,046
God forbid,
that you would live in this house.

680
01:33:54,047 --> 01:33:56,566
Don't speak like that.

681
01:33:56,567 --> 01:33:58,886
What have you become.

682
01:33:58,887 --> 01:34:02,886
You were honest once.
Now you changed for the worse.

683
01:34:02,887 --> 01:34:06,526
What am I like, grandma?

684
01:34:06,527 --> 01:34:09,126
You've broken my heart.

685
01:34:09,127 --> 01:34:15,127
You've spoilt entirely.

686
01:34:21,647 --> 01:34:25,606
Let me tell you something son.
All this is a fata morgana.

687
01:34:25,607 --> 01:34:27,766
You gave me money.

688
01:34:27,767 --> 01:34:31,326
I may die tomorrow.
Who will return you?

689
01:34:31,327 --> 01:34:37,327
Take the money back.

690
01:34:45,447 --> 01:34:48,886
You've burnt your hand!
You know how that hurts.

691
01:34:48,887 --> 01:34:54,887
You're doing yourself evil things.

692
01:35:07,967 --> 01:35:11,166
Stop playing!
You're playing madness.

693
01:35:11,167 --> 01:35:14,366
You'll kill a man.
Back!

694
01:35:14,367 --> 01:35:20,367
Perhan, wait for me.

695
01:35:21,687 --> 01:35:26,046
Neighbour, you're blind drunk!

696
01:35:26,047 --> 01:35:29,086
What are you looking at?
Get in!

697
01:35:29,087 --> 01:35:35,087
My neighbour is my concern.

698
01:36:23,647 --> 01:36:29,647
Chandelier!

699
01:36:30,007 --> 01:36:36,007
Scales!

700
01:36:36,407 --> 01:36:41,766
Cooker!

701
01:36:41,767 --> 01:36:47,767
This present is from a wedding witness.
Let's see what's inside.

702
01:36:48,327 --> 01:36:54,327
A bit of silence, please.

703
01:36:57,967 --> 01:37:03,967
Bread!
Money! Gold!

704
01:37:05,247 --> 01:37:09,606
A limuosine is coming.

705
01:37:09,607 --> 01:37:12,766
The chauffeur
is opening the door.

706
01:37:12,767 --> 01:37:17,686
The bride is stepping out.

707
01:37:17,687 --> 01:37:21,726
The groom is carrying her in his arms.

708
01:37:21,727 --> 01:37:26,206
Mother-in-law is offering the daughter-in-law
bread and sugar,

709
01:37:26,207 --> 01:37:30,566
so she would have a sweet life.

710
01:37:30,567 --> 01:37:32,966
Be happy.

711
01:37:32,967 --> 01:37:36,886
The groom kisses the bride.

712
01:37:36,887 --> 01:37:41,286
Mother-in-law leads daughter-in-law into the house.

713
01:37:41,287 --> 01:37:44,966
The groom is being beaten to obtain 
power.

714
01:37:44,967 --> 01:37:50,967
He'll need it.

715
01:38:40,807 --> 01:38:45,686
Grandma and her grandson will 
now dance.

716
01:38:45,687 --> 01:38:48,126
How beautiful he is,
how elegant,

717
01:38:48,127 --> 01:38:54,127
wise, civilized and
pedantic!

718
01:38:54,287 --> 01:39:00,287
Grandma's grandson.
My living monument.

719
01:39:08,087 --> 01:39:14,087
Get up, come with me.

720
01:39:15,047 --> 01:39:18,406
You and Ruza
must help me.

721
01:39:18,407 --> 01:39:21,406
Find some cripples to go
begging

722
01:39:21,407 --> 01:39:25,046
and a pregnant woman with the same fate,
as mine has.

723
01:39:25,047 --> 01:39:29,646
Here's your advance.

724
01:39:29,647 --> 01:39:32,326
We'll find some cripples.

725
01:39:32,327 --> 01:39:36,846
And how do you intend to sell your own
child?

726
01:39:36,847 --> 01:39:39,646
You will meet with a terrible accident.

727
01:39:39,647 --> 01:39:42,326
First, the child is not mine.

728
01:39:42,327 --> 01:39:46,086
I will bring up no bastard.
And second, I won't repeat.

729
01:39:46,087 --> 01:39:50,766
Only under these conditions
will I marry her.

730
01:39:50,767 --> 01:39:56,767
Go out so they won't see us.

731
01:40:27,647 --> 01:40:30,366
Are you building another house
here?

732
01:40:30,367 --> 01:40:36,367
If we built it you would see it.
A house is not a needle.

733
01:41:12,207 --> 01:41:16,046
If there is a God,
the kids will go into the world,

734
01:41:16,047 --> 01:41:21,046
to work and earn money.
They just musn't disgrace themselves.

735
01:41:21,047 --> 01:41:24,486
Let them build a house
like other people,

736
01:41:24,487 --> 01:41:27,646
with their own labor
by the sweat of their face.

737
01:41:27,647 --> 01:41:29,806
I am already old.
I can't work anymore.

738
01:41:29,807 --> 01:41:35,807
Why not?
They're still young.

739
01:41:38,087 --> 01:41:40,686
You know we burn lime.

740
01:41:40,687 --> 01:41:45,086
Merdzan doesn't want to work.

741
01:41:45,087 --> 01:41:48,846
May I come to you?

742
01:41:48,847 --> 01:41:52,926
Not even dead.

743
01:41:52,927 --> 01:41:56,646
Did you understand?

744
01:41:56,647 --> 01:42:01,726
I can hardly wait that Perhan, my 
sweetheart, returns.

745
01:42:01,727 --> 01:42:04,206
I can hardly wait that he gets
a child.

746
01:42:04,207 --> 01:42:06,686
So that this wish of mine
turns true as well.

747
01:42:06,687 --> 01:42:09,206
Do with me whatever you want.
But why?

748
01:42:09,207 --> 01:42:11,206
You know well why.

749
01:42:11,207 --> 01:42:16,686
Don't foist me a magpie instead of
a gosling.

750
01:42:16,687 --> 01:42:21,286
This child is diligent,
obedient, qualified.

751
01:42:21,287 --> 01:42:23,886
I'm sorry for speaking about this.

752
01:42:23,887 --> 01:42:29,846
Something is pressing me in my soul,
so words are like a cure.

753
01:42:29,847 --> 01:42:32,366
My son comes at midnight,
the house is for him like an inn.

754
01:42:32,367 --> 01:42:35,166
He eats and goes to the whores.

755
01:42:35,167 --> 01:42:38,046
I don't know what's wrong with him.

756
01:42:38,047 --> 01:42:41,766
My golden one, Perhan,
is the best person in this world.

757
01:42:41,767 --> 01:42:45,646
He's not like my son, bastard.

758
01:42:45,647 --> 01:42:49,246
If you knew what kind of daughter I 
had.

759
01:42:49,247 --> 01:42:52,966
His mother was a beauty.

760
01:42:52,967 --> 01:42:57,326
He looks just like her.

761
01:42:57,327 --> 01:43:01,406
She died young.
I fell ill because of her.

762
01:43:01,407 --> 01:43:07,407
What should I tell you?

763
01:45:45,647 --> 01:45:48,326
Are you alive? -I'm alive.

764
01:45:48,327 --> 01:45:54,327
Here, eat.

765
01:46:39,727 --> 01:46:42,206
Perhan, you must believe me.

766
01:46:42,207 --> 01:46:44,606
The child is ours.

767
01:46:44,607 --> 01:46:47,806
Merdzan assaulted me
when I was three months pregnant.

768
01:46:47,807 --> 01:46:50,326
Don't lie.
Shut up, don't lie.

769
01:46:50,327 --> 01:46:53,046
I'm not lying. -I don't want to 
bring up a bastard!

770
01:46:53,047 --> 01:46:59,047
I will sell him. Then will make our
own child.

771
01:47:14,207 --> 01:47:19,486
Give me your hand.

772
01:47:19,487 --> 01:47:25,487
This one is ours too. Believe yourself,
if you don't believe me.

773
01:47:25,887 --> 01:47:29,726
I concieved when we slept together on
St. George's Day.

774
01:47:29,727 --> 01:47:31,806
I've calculated everything.

775
01:47:31,807 --> 01:47:35,286
I swear by my life.
I know he's a bastard.

776
01:47:35,287 --> 01:47:38,566
We'll make our own.
I said what I said.

777
01:47:38,567 --> 01:47:41,486
Why? This one is ours too.

778
01:47:41,487 --> 01:47:47,487
Wait.

779
01:47:59,207 --> 01:48:04,566
Something in me has
turned upside down.

780
01:48:04,567 --> 01:48:08,006
I dreamt that you gave birth to
a white bird.

781
01:48:08,007 --> 01:48:12,766
When I came near.

782
01:48:12,767 --> 01:48:18,767
Wait.

783
01:48:26,567 --> 01:48:29,326
What do you want?

784
01:48:29,327 --> 01:48:31,366
You've done everything well.

785
01:48:31,367 --> 01:48:37,367
But where is a wife for me?

786
01:48:37,527 --> 01:48:40,126
Couldn't you find her?

787
01:48:40,127 --> 01:48:42,526
Where is my house?

788
01:48:42,527 --> 01:48:45,806
Why did you lie about building
a house for me?

789
01:48:45,807 --> 01:48:48,566
Were you at home?

790
01:48:48,567 --> 01:48:52,886
From where would I bring my wife 
then?

791
01:48:52,887 --> 01:48:56,406
I thought.
- What did you think?

792
01:48:56,407 --> 01:48:59,766
That you picked up one on the way.
What do i know.

793
01:48:59,767 --> 01:49:04,726
You know, Ahmed.
You know everything.

794
01:49:04,727 --> 01:49:10,727
Why did you lie to me?
- Sadam lied to me!

795
01:49:12,327 --> 01:49:15,206
I gave him the money for
your house.

796
01:49:15,207 --> 01:49:18,006
He put it into his own pocket.

797
01:49:18,007 --> 01:49:22,326
He came yesterday to laugh in
my face.

798
01:49:22,327 --> 01:49:25,606
I'm sorry, I'm not responsible for
your house.

799
01:49:25,607 --> 01:49:30,566
I swear by my child.

800
01:49:30,567 --> 01:49:34,046
Believe me. If you don't want to,
go. Leave me alone.

801
01:49:34,047 --> 01:49:40,047
May I die.

802
01:50:07,167 --> 01:50:10,406
I will give you half of
my house.

803
01:50:10,407 --> 01:50:12,926
Here are the papers.

804
01:50:12,927 --> 01:50:17,966
I will call the lawyer tomorrow
so they will certify it in court.

805
01:50:17,967 --> 01:50:22,486
I may not be much long.

806
01:50:22,487 --> 01:50:27,646
And Robert?

807
01:50:27,647 --> 01:50:32,646
I loved him more then life. And now?

808
01:50:32,647 --> 01:50:34,406
I don't know.

809
01:50:34,407 --> 01:50:38,126
I obsere him every day and 
everything seems suspicious to me.

810
01:50:38,127 --> 01:50:42,526
The eyes, the nose, hands.

811
01:50:42,527 --> 01:50:48,527
He doesn't look like me in any way.

812
01:50:56,487 --> 01:51:02,487
We're brothers in that way as well -
the wives cheated on us both.

813
01:53:29,007 --> 01:53:35,007
Boy!

814
01:53:44,167 --> 01:53:47,726
Look, Perhan!
A boy!

815
01:53:47,727 --> 01:53:53,727
Let us not bewitch him.

816
01:54:08,647 --> 01:54:14,647
Azra!

817
01:54:29,927 --> 01:54:36,400
No, Azra. I ask you like God,
don't leave me!

818
01:54:37,967 --> 01:54:43,967
I love you! Azra!

819
01:55:14,327 --> 01:55:18,766
God is nevertheless
a blind cat.

820
01:55:18,767 --> 01:55:22,006
He looked at me while I was hiding 
treasure in the canal.

821
01:55:22,007 --> 01:55:24,406
He tied my sould with a rope
and let

822
01:55:24,407 --> 01:55:27,606
the flood wash away
the gold and money.

823
01:55:27,607 --> 01:55:29,806
First he gave me
wealth,

824
01:55:29,807 --> 01:55:34,046
in the end with the treasure
he took my soul as well.

825
01:55:34,047 --> 01:55:36,686
I had so much gold,
dear Hatidza,

826
01:55:36,687 --> 01:55:39,326
that I could build a house out
of gold coins.

827
01:55:39,327 --> 01:55:42,406
and cover the roof with them.

828
01:55:42,407 --> 01:55:45,846
We could build a big house,

829
01:55:45,847 --> 01:55:50,126
we could touch the moon from
its roof.

830
01:55:50,127 --> 01:55:54,286
A cruel fate has come upon me.

831
01:55:54,287 --> 01:55:57,846
The more I rack my brain about
where it came from,

832
01:55:57,847 --> 01:56:00,926
the bigger is the earthquake
in my head

833
01:56:00,927 --> 01:56:04,366
and the more I go away from
the truth.

834
01:56:04,367 --> 01:56:07,246
Maybe you have also put a spell
on me, grandma Tidza

835
01:56:07,247 --> 01:56:09,926
when I told you that I don't
trust anyone anymore,

836
01:56:09,927 --> 01:56:12,646
when I caught myself lying.

837
01:56:12,647 --> 01:56:15,566
You told me then:

838
01:56:15,567 --> 01:56:18,566
If you don't trust at all,
God will abandon you.

839
01:56:18,567 --> 01:56:22,406
You won't be good nor to God
nor to people.

840
01:56:22,407 --> 01:56:25,086
You know, I am not like that
good to people,

841
01:56:25,087 --> 01:56:27,926
but i was deceived by a man,

842
01:56:27,927 --> 01:56:32,486
whom I trusted more then God.

843
01:56:32,487 --> 01:56:36,446
Ahmed was both God and father
for me.

844
01:56:36,447 --> 01:56:40,526
I wrote to you that Daca
stayed at the hospital.

845
01:56:40,527 --> 01:56:44,046
Even your own eyes
can decieve yourself.

846
01:56:44,047 --> 01:56:48,326
If I could, I would
put out my eyes and get blind.

847
01:56:48,327 --> 01:56:50,766
Only later I have realised,

848
01:56:50,767 --> 01:56:56,767
what a trap Ahmed set me up.

849
01:57:00,887 --> 01:57:03,486
Where is he?
- He ran away. -Where?

850
01:57:03,487 --> 01:57:06,326
Who knows. He drove me away
and found himself another woman.

851
01:57:06,327 --> 01:57:08,606
Dzamila, talk, if you know.

852
01:57:08,607 --> 01:57:14,607
He has reconciled with his brothers.
They united the slaves and disappeared.

853
01:57:15,607 --> 01:57:19,046
Did you take my sister from
Ljubljana?

854
01:57:19,047 --> 01:57:21,486
Where? Speak, I'll kill you!

855
01:57:21,487 --> 01:57:27,246
Leave him alone, you fool!

856
01:57:27,247 --> 01:57:31,126
To Rome.

857
01:57:31,127 --> 01:57:37,127
May God give you luck.
Help the poor girl.

858
01:57:53,327 --> 01:57:57,806
Did you see this girl?
- No, I don't know her.

859
01:57:57,807 --> 01:57:59,486
Fuck you!

860
01:57:59,487 --> 01:58:02,406
Fuck you, asshole!

861
01:58:02,407 --> 01:58:05,566
You said I shouldn't return
home without Danira.

862
01:58:05,567 --> 01:58:07,766
I travelled the whole world from end
to end.

863
01:58:07,767 --> 01:58:10,046
Ahmed as though as he would turn
into a mole,

864
01:58:10,047 --> 01:58:12,286
and Danira is nowhere to be seen.

865
01:58:12,287 --> 01:58:14,726
I've been looking for Ahmed for 
three years.

866
01:58:14,727 --> 01:58:17,966
I'd like to live 300 years,
just to find him

867
01:58:17,967 --> 01:58:20,326
and pull out his heart.

868
01:58:20,327 --> 01:58:22,206
I've been searching for her for
days.

869
01:58:22,207 --> 01:58:24,326
This has made me turn into wind,

870
01:58:24,327 --> 01:58:26,566
my dreams have evaporated like dust.

871
01:58:26,567 --> 01:58:28,806
I can't dream anymore.

872
01:58:28,807 --> 01:58:31,046
A gypsy without dreams is like
a church without a roof,

873
01:58:31,047 --> 01:58:37,047
like a textbook without letters.
Yours, Perhan.

874
01:59:42,207 --> 01:59:48,207
Danira!

875
01:59:58,047 --> 02:00:04,047
Perhan!

876
02:00:19,047 --> 02:00:23,046
Brother!

877
02:00:23,047 --> 02:00:24,966
God!

878
02:00:24,967 --> 02:00:30,967
As long as I have found you!

879
02:00:42,807 --> 02:00:46,046
And your leg? Does it hurt?

880
02:00:46,047 --> 02:00:52,047
Same.

881
02:00:52,047 --> 02:00:58,047
Oh my.

882
02:01:01,167 --> 02:01:04,566
You know what happened? -What?

883
02:01:04,567 --> 02:01:07,926
He said that the hospitals in Italy
are better.

884
02:01:07,927 --> 02:01:10,526
That they will admit us here .

885
02:01:10,527 --> 02:01:13,046
That you and I will be together.

886
02:01:13,047 --> 02:01:18,126
Since then I have been begging.
He have travlled over 101 cities.

887
02:01:18,127 --> 02:01:22,086
Today he's getting married.
- Ahmed? -Yes.

888
02:01:22,087 --> 02:01:28,087
And you have a son.

889
02:01:28,927 --> 02:01:31,846
He's just like you.

890
02:01:31,847 --> 02:01:37,847
They're waiting that he grows up,
so they can sell him.

891
02:01:49,847 --> 02:01:55,847
Perhan!

892
02:02:10,247 --> 02:02:16,247
What is it?

893
02:02:46,927 --> 02:02:50,286
What's your name?
- Perhan. And yours?

894
02:02:50,287 --> 02:02:52,046
Perhan.

895
02:02:52,047 --> 02:02:58,047
Don't lie! Why are you lying?

896
02:02:58,207 --> 02:03:04,207
Hurry up, please.
Go, they will see us..

897
02:03:15,207 --> 02:03:21,207
This is your father.
Give him your hand.

898
02:03:25,487 --> 02:03:27,886
Wait for me here.
I'll be right back.

899
02:03:27,887 --> 02:03:30,006
Don't go anywhere,
please.

900
02:03:30,007 --> 02:03:33,046
I must buy a gift for
grandma.

901
02:03:33,047 --> 02:03:36,486
Come back soon. Buy her a dishwashing
sponge.

902
02:03:36,487 --> 02:03:39,246
Don't forget about my accordion.
- Don't worry.

903
02:03:39,247 --> 02:03:42,006
If I'm late, I will catch up
with you on the next stattion.

904
02:03:42,007 --> 02:03:48,007
Take it.

905
02:03:50,327 --> 02:03:55,126
What's wrong?
- I'm sad.

906
02:03:55,127 --> 02:04:01,127
Don't be. Let' wave to him.

907
02:04:02,447 --> 02:04:06,766
Daddy!

908
02:04:06,767 --> 02:04:12,767
Perhan, stop!

909
02:04:14,007 --> 02:04:18,206
I am angry with you. -Why?

910
02:04:18,207 --> 02:04:23,166
You won't return,
you won't buy me an accordion

911
02:04:23,167 --> 02:04:28,566
Let me be damned,
If I don't return.

912
02:04:28,567 --> 02:04:33,326
Go now.

913
02:04:33,327 --> 02:04:39,327
Go.

914
02:05:29,487 --> 02:05:32,686
Irfan!

915
02:05:32,687 --> 02:05:38,687
Is it you, Perhan?

916
02:05:40,287 --> 02:05:44,006
Help me. -Don't worry.

917
02:05:44,007 --> 02:05:49,526
What cigarettes do you smoke?

918
02:05:49,527 --> 02:05:55,527
Good cigarettes!

919
02:05:55,767 --> 02:06:01,767
Cover my back.
- Don't' you worry.

920
02:06:37,407 --> 02:06:42,526
Ahmed, good luck!

921
02:06:42,527 --> 02:06:48,527
Dance, Ahmed!

922
02:07:32,847 --> 02:07:38,006
Where are you, birdie?
Look at him, Ahmed.

923
02:07:38,007 --> 02:07:41,406
Where are you, Perhan,
my child?

924
02:07:41,407 --> 02:07:44,446
I've come to you.
I'll serve you till I die.

925
02:07:44,447 --> 02:07:47,006
You are my father.
You and God.

926
02:07:47,007 --> 02:07:49,686
Accept me or kill me.

927
02:07:49,687 --> 02:07:52,006
Why would I kill you, you poor fellow?

928
02:07:52,007 --> 02:07:55,446
Kill me, sinful thoughts have come
to my mind.

929
02:07:55,447 --> 02:07:58,926
Give him food to eat.
Look how thin he is.

930
02:07:58,927 --> 02:08:04,927
Who is this?
- Some fool, a poor man.

931
02:09:01,727 --> 02:09:07,727
Eat the cake!

932
02:09:24,327 --> 02:09:30,327
Die in shit!

933
02:10:40,287 --> 02:10:43,126
Hurry up.

934
02:10:43,127 --> 02:10:49,127
Quick, to the bridge.

935
02:10:52,927 --> 02:10:58,927
I will kill you
for preventing my marriage!

936
02:11:32,927 --> 02:11:38,927
Run.

937
02:11:44,687 --> 02:11:48,446
You've ruined my youth,
and I'll destroy your head.

938
02:11:48,447 --> 02:11:51,886
Let it be, what shall be.

939
02:11:51,887 --> 02:11:57,887
I will catch up with you,
even if you were a bird.

940
02:12:02,167 --> 02:12:08,167
For fuck sake!

941
02:15:45,487 --> 02:15:49,766
Oh, God!

942
02:15:49,767 --> 02:15:55,767
God, what have you done?

943
02:16:02,247 --> 02:16:08,247
You have turned as though
the whole world has turned.

944
02:16:09,247 --> 02:16:15,247
Merdzan will lift you up again,
but you must help me.

945
02:16:16,127 --> 02:16:22,127
If you can't,
I'll lift you up myself.

946
02:16:28,407 --> 02:16:31,886
Did you see Perhan?
Why?

947
02:16:31,887 --> 02:16:35,806
He left you without a father
and mother,

948
02:16:35,807 --> 02:16:41,126
but he washed your feet.

949
02:16:41,127 --> 02:16:47,127
He didn't know how to call you.
You let him among the wolves.

950
02:16:48,047 --> 02:16:54,236
Lead him where you think 
is the best place in that world.

951
02:17:02,927 --> 02:17:05,726
Do you see these two dices?

952
02:17:05,727 --> 02:17:08,326
Let them fall,

953
02:17:08,327 --> 02:17:12,366
for once let them fall,
as I wish.

954
02:17:12,367 --> 02:17:16,206
My wish would come true.

955
02:17:16,207 --> 02:17:21,486
And may I not be Merdzan anymore,
if I don't fulfill your wish.

956
02:17:21,487 --> 02:17:27,487
And throw the dices like they should be.

957
02:17:31,487 --> 02:17:36,046
Translation by:
Bluester

